article.headline: Toledo 76, Buffalo 63
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio (AP) -- Tyrone Kent scored 22 points and had seven rebounds to lead Toledo to a 76-63 win over Buffalo on Saturday night. Jonathan Amos added 20 points and Jerrah Young contributed 10 for the Rockets (6-12, 3-3), who trailed by four with 13:05 left in the first half but outscored Buffalo 26-15 the rest of the period. Sean Smiley scored 21 points for Buffalo, who committed 20 turnovers leading to 25 Toledo points. Andy Robinson added 14 points for the Bulls (6-12, 0-6). Toledo shot 45.7 percent from the field but only 27.8 percent from behind the 3-point line. Buffalo shot 38.7 percent overall but was just 7-of-15 (46.7 percent) from the free-throw line. Buffalo spread out its scoring attack, getting 45 points from their bench to Toledo's eight points.
